MARTEILIOSIS, OYSTERS - MOROCCO: OIE ALERT
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat, 12 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Alert message, 11 Aug 2006 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/060811MAR.htm>

Translation of information received on 9 Aug 2006 from Dr Hamid
Benazzou, Director of Animal Production Department, Ministry of
Agriculture and Rural Development, Rabat:
Report date: 3 Aug 2006.
Reason for immediate notification: 1st occurrence in a country or
zone/department of the country, if the country or zone/department of
the country was previously considered to be free of that particular disease.
Identification of agent: _Marteilia refringens_.
Host species: flat oyster (_Ostrea edulis_).
Date of first confirmation of the event: 17 Jul 2006.
Date of start of the event: 13 Apr 2006.
An outbreak of infection with _Marteilia refringens_ has been
reported in a lagoon in Atalayoun (Nador province) in wild flat
oysters in a semi-closed farming system.
The diagnosis was made using histopathological examination by the
National Fisheries Research Institute in Morocco and the IFREMER (OIE
reference laboratory for mollusc diseases) in France.
Control measures undertaken:
- within-country movement controls,
- strengthening epidemiological surveillance in zone 1 (Saidia, Cap
de Trois Fourches) according to the animal health supervision program.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[_M. refringens_ is a lethal protistan parasite of the European flat
oyster, _Ostrea edulis_. Its geographic distribution is: France,
Greece, Italy, Morocco, Portugal, and Spain.
For the Nador province, northeastern Morocco, on the Mediterranean,
see map at <http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/morocco.pdf>.
Interested subscribers will find information on the pathological and
diagnostic aspects of Marteiliosis, including a reference list, in
chapter 3.1.3. of OIE's Manual of Diagnostic Tests for Aquatic
Animals, 2003, available at
<http://www.oie.int/eng/normes/fmanual/A_00039.htm>.- Mod.AS]
[Image of imprint of flat oyster _Ostrea edulis_ digestive gland with
young stages (1) and advanced stages (2) of the parasite _Marteilia
refringens_ (Hemacolor staining) at:
<http://www.ifremer.fr/crlmollusc/images/martei1.jpg> - Mod.JW]
